{{Quote|Brief periods of instantaneous communication won't endanger our location...not so long as the ion-scrambler is operating to confuse the enemy.|C-3PO|<ref name="Star Wars (1977) 9">[[Star Wars (1977) 9|''Star Wars'' (1977) 9]]</ref>}}
'''Ion-scramblers''' were devices that were used while making [[Subspace transceiver/Legends|transceiver]] transmissions in order to scramble the source of the communication. This ensured that unwanted listeners would not be able to track the location of a signal's origin point. The [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] used ion-scramblers to keep their whereabouts hidden from the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]].

